dc_title_s: Hydro (Polygon and Line) Florence County, WI 2020
dc_description_s: This data represents hydrography for Florence County, Wisconsin in 2020, and includes the layers 'FLORENCE_HYDRO_2020_LINE' and 'FLORENCE_HYDRO_2020_POLY'. For line: [This shapefile includes all line features (arcs) in the 1:24,000-scale Hydrography data model (Version 5). The arcs are attributed to easily define themes based on cartographic or modeling needs. Arc attributes include feature names and Water Body ID Codes (WBICs). The Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources (DNR) developed this statewide Hydrography geographic data layer from 1:24,000-scale sources. The 1:24K Hydrography database includes information about surface water features represented on the US Geological Survey's 1:24,000-scale topographic map series such as perennial and intermittent streams, lakes, and so on. A large portion of the DNR's Waterbody Identification Codes (WBICs) have been incorporated into the 24K Hydro layer, along with surface water names from the USGS Geographic Names Information System (GNIS) database. Wetlands delineations are NOT included in the 24K Hydro data layer.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison.
